{
  "texts": [
    "Next, a k NN classifier's LOO influence is calculated exactly (Jia et al., 2021, Lemma 1) using these extracted features.",
    "prove that kNN LOO influence only requires O(n log n) time-significantly faster in practice than vanilla LOO's O(nT) complexity.",
    "also demonstrate empirically that kNN LOO and vanilla LOO gener- ate similar influence rankings across various learning domains and tasks.",
    "Efficient LOO estimation in decision tree ensembles Sharchilev et al. (2018) propose leafRefit, an efficient LOO estimator for decision-tree ensembles.",
    "leafRefit's efficiency derives from the simplifying assumption that instance deletions do not affect the trees' structure."
  ]
}